history.content:
This path is pretty common (and I have done it myself).

Taking 126 a year before 189 is fine; I used 127 much more in 189 so it was better to have taken 127 right before.

126 is not used as much, at least in this semester's 189 (mostly just the mathematical maturity etc.)

A lot of 126 is not directly applicable to 189, at least relative to 127. That being said, it's definitely good to have taken it sometime before 189, and it's definitely not necessary to remember much from 126.

children.subject: From my personal experience, it is pretty easy to be rusty with probability. However, it gets way easier each time you pick it up again. Don’t worry about it and just enjoy the process. 126 is more of a modeling class than a pure probability class like 134 anyway. I would say 127 is much more relevant to 189 than 126, so your plan sounds good!

history.content: I plan on taking eecs 126 this next semester while taking 127 the semester after that. My worries is by the time I take 189 which will be after 127, I will have become rusty with 126. Would it be better to take 126 and 127 concurrently before 189 rather than one a semester? Thanks!
